            <title><![CDATA[GTA 6 Trailer Includes PlayStation Controller And Console References]]></title>
            <link>https://www.gamespot.com/articles/gta-6-trailer-includes-playstation-controller-and-console-references/1100-6531330/?ftag=CAD-01-10abi2f</link>
            <guid>https://www.resetera.com/threads/gta-6-trailer-includes-playstation-controller-and-console-references.1182225/</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[https://www.gamespot.com/articles/gta-6-trailer-includes-playstation-controller-and-console-references/1100-6531330/?ftag=CAD-01-10abi2f<br/><br/><div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><p>
    <span data-nosnippet="">GameSpot may receive revenue from affiliate and advertising partnerships for sharing this content and from purchases through links.</span>
  </p><article itemscope="" data-type-id="1100" data-guid="1100-6531330">

            
            
  


        

  


        
        
              <section>

                  
          <div data-content-element-selector="p, .js-buylink-item-container" data-allowed-classes-selector="js-buylink-item-container">
                <p>The new <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/grand-theft-auto-6-everything-we-know/1100-6503729/" data-ref-id="1100-6503729">GTA 6</a> <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/gta-6-gets-a-new-trailer/1100-6531329/" data-ref-id="1100-6531329">trailer</a> that just arrived contains multiple nods to PlayStation. Not only was the footage captured on PlayStation 5, but the trailer itself features what look like DualSense controllers and a stand-in for a PlayStation console.</p><p>In a sequence where Lucia gets home and greets Jason, we see two DualSense-like controllers sitting on a glass table, with what looks like a mock PS5 in the background.</p><figure data-align="center" data-size="large" data-img-src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1179/11799911/4489126-screenshot2025-05-06at10.59.58am.png" data-ref-id="1300-4489126" data-ratio="0.60762607626076" data-width="813" data-embed-type="image"><a href="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1179/11799911/4489126-screenshot2025-05-06at10.59.58am.png" data-ref-id="1300-4489126"></a><figcaption>Is that a PlayStation console in the GTA 6 trailer?</figcaption><img src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1179/11799911/4489126-screenshot2025-05-06at10.59.58am.png"></figure><p>These details, along with the disclaimer that the footage was captured on PS5, is leading some to believe that Sony and Rockstar Games might have some kind of co-marketing deal for GTA 6.</p><p>This wouldn't be totally surprising, of course, as GTA and PlayStation have been linked together for years, going back decades. <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/playstation-was-worried-about-xbox-which-prompted-gta-exclusivity-deals/1100-6528282/" data-ref-id="1100-6528282">GTA 3, Vice City, and San Andreas all first launched exclusively on PlayStation consoles</a> because Sony paid Rockstar for that.</p><p>While the exclusivity deals ended there--GTA 4 and GTA 5 launched on PlayStation and Xbox at the same time--Sony did continue to work with Rockstar on special deals. For example, GTA 5 was <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/e3-2014-grand-theft-auto-v-coming-to-playstation-4-xbox-one-pc/1100-6420294/" data-ref-id="1100-6420294">announced for PS4 at Sony's E3 briefing in 2014</a>.</p><figure data-align="center" data-size="large" data-img-src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1179/11799911/4489130-screenshot2025-05-06at11.00.11am.png" data-ref-id="1300-4489130" data-ratio="0.59605911330049" data-width="812" data-embed-type="image"><a href="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1179/11799911/4489130-screenshot2025-05-06at11.00.11am.png" data-ref-id="1300-4489130"></a><figcaption>It looks like Jason and Lucia have a PlayStation console and controllers at their house.</figcaption><img src="https://www.gamespot.com/a/uploads/original/1179/11799911/4489130-screenshot2025-05-06at11.00.11am.png"></figure><p>Following a <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/gta-6-delayed-to-2026/1100-6531282/" data-ref-id="1100-6531282">high-profile delay</a>, GTA 6 is now set for release in May 2026 for PS5 and Xbox Series X|S. In the meantime, you can take a look at <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/gallery/gta-6-screenshots-images/2900-6525/" data-ref-id="2900-6525">more than 150 new images from the game</a> in the gallery below. We've also rounded up all of the <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/gallery/every-grand-theft-auto-6-character-revealed/2900-6537/" data-ref-id="2900-6537">GTA 6 characters</a> and <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/gallery/gta-6-all-main-locations-from-vice-city-and-beyond/2900-6538/" data-ref-id="2900-6538">main locations</a> revealed so far.</p>
  
                        
    
        
        
  
